{"type":"message","id":"4b664417","parentId":"85781f7f","timestamp":"2026-02-15T18:40:29.183Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 20:40 GMT+2] OPERATION: HONEST AUDIT V3.1 (5-MIN ITERATION).\n\n1.  **Proof of Work (File Check):**\n    *   `read src/core/shm_manager.py` (first 20 lines).\n    *   `read src/core/rate_limiter.py` (first 20 lines).\n    *   `read docs/AUTONOMOUS_BACKLOG.md`.\n    *   *Self-Correction:* If missing -> Create stubs immediately.\n\n2.  **Short Stress Test (5 Min):**\n    *   Modify/Create `tests/endurance_test.py`:\n        *   Duration: 300s.\n        *   Log: `print(f\"[Status] RAM: {process.memory_info().rss / 1024 / 1024:.2f} MB, Latency: {latency*1000:.4f} ms\")`.\n    *   Execute.\n\n3.  **Instant OODA (Log Analysis):**\n    *   `tail -n 50 logs/performance_audit.log`.\n    *   *Identify:* Max Jitter (Peak - Avg).\n    *   *Errors:* Check for `BrokenPipe`, `SharedMemory`.\n\n4.  **Reporting Hook:**\n    *   Call `generate_final_report()`.\n    *   Commit: `test: 5min-endurance-success`.\n\n5.  **Output:**\n    *   Code snippets (Proof).\n    *   Metrics (Avg Latency, RAM trend).\n    *   Next Backlog Item.\n    *   Commit Hash."}],"timestamp":1771180829181}}
{"type":"message","id":"7a273e15","parentId":"4b664417","timestamp":"2026-02-15T18:40:38.249Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Reflecting on the Plan**\n\nI've been meticulously reviewing the user's requirements for the \"Honest Audit V3.1\". The core focus now is understanding the file structure and the initial checks that need to be performed. Specifically, I'm focusing on parsing the `src/core/shm_manager.py`, `src/core/rate_limiter.py`, and `docs/AUTONOMOUS_BACKLOG.md` files as a starting point. This initial assessment seems crucial.\n\n\n**Prioritizing File Handling**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the file check procedure. The key is to ensure the existence of the three specified files and create basic stubs if any are missing. I am considering the most efficient approach, in terms of libraries and their corresponding benefits, for this initial assessment. Afterwards, I'll need to define how to log the metrics to be included in the endurance test.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771180838011_170","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/core/shm_manager.py","limit":20},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771180838117_171","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/core/rate_limiter.py","limit":20}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771180838243_172","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"docs/AUTONOMOUS_BACKLOG.md"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":4822,"output":182,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":5004,"cost":{"input":0.009644,"output":0.002184,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.011828}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771180829183}}
{"type":"message","id":"de0e8e13","parentId":"7a273e15","timestamp":"2026-02-15T18:40:38.271Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771180838011_170","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\nfrom multiprocessing import shared_memory\nimport logging\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\nclass SHMManager:\n    def __init__(self, name=\"prices_shm\", create=True):\n        self.name = name\n        # [CS2_Price, Rust_Price, TF2_Price, Dota_Price]\n        self.init_data = [0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0] \n        self.sl = None\n        if create:\n            self._create()\n        else:\n            self._attach()\n\n    def _create(self):\n        try:\n            self.sl = shared_memory.ShareableList(self.init_data, name=self.name)\n\n[34 more lines in file. Use offset=21 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771180838270}}
{"type":"message","id":"666210de","parentId":"de0e8e13","timestamp":"2026-02-15T18:40:38.276Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771180838117_171","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import asyncio\nimport time\nfrom typing import Dict, Optional\n\nclass AdaptiveRateLimiter:\n    def __init__(self, default_delay: float = 0.5):\n        self.current_delay = default_delay\n        self.remaining = 100  # Default assumption\n        self.limit = 100      # Default assumption\n        self.reset_time = 0\n\n    async def acquire(self):\n        \"\"\"Wait for the appropriate delay based on current rate limit status.\"\"\"\n        if self.current_delay > 0:\n            await asyncio.sleep(self.current_delay)\n\n    def update_from_headers(self, headers: Dict[str, str]):\n        \"\"\"Update rate limit status from response headers.\"\"\"\n        # Normalize headers to lowercase keys for case-insensitive lookup\n        headers_lower = {k.lower(): v for k, v in headers.items()}\n\n[33 more lines in file. Use offset=21 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771180838274}}
{"type":"message","id":"4aea794a","parentId":"666210de","timestamp":"2026-02-15T18:40:38.280Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771180838243_172","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# AUTONOMOUS BACKLOG (PARETO 5)\n\nThis document contains the 5 critical tasks identified as the Pareto set for immediate impact.\n\n1.  **[CRITICAL] Rust Link Integration**\n    *   **Goal:** Replace Python HMAC/signing logic with `dmarket_rust_core`.\n    *   **Status:** Pending (Fallback active: PYTHON_LEGACY).\n    *   **Action:** Ensure `dmarket_rust_core` compiles via maturin and bind to `src/dmarket/api/client.py`.\n\n2.  **[HIGH] WebSocket Stability**\n    *   **Goal:** Improve reconnection logic and heartbeat handling for DMarket WS.\n    *   **Current Issue:** Frequent disconnects under load.\n    *   **Action:** Implement exponential backoff and connection pooling.\n\n3.  **[HIGH] SHM Optimization (Shared Memory)**\n    *   **Goal:** Use shared memory for high-frequency data (prices, inventory).\n    *   **Action:** Implement Python `multiprocessing.shared_memory` or Redis-backed buffer.\n\n4.  **[MEDIUM] Profit Telemetry**\n    *   **Goal:** Real-time dashboard for profit/loss calculation.\n    *   **Action:** Add Prometheus metrics for trade execution P&L.\n\n5.  **[MEDIUM] Error Handling & Circuit Breaker**\n    *   **Goal:** Robust error handling for API failures.\n    *   **Action:** Refine `api_circuit_breaker.py` thresholds and add specific exception types for retry logic.\n\n---\n*Generated by Subagent Flash during Manual Resuscitation.*\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771180838279}}
